Add.Title: Business life in Copenhagen
Add.Description: Copenhagen: Combining work and family life is a different experience and a pleasantly positive surprise for many – and highly appealing to professionals. In Copenhagen you can have a career that is on track as well as a fulfilling family life. Photographer: Tuala Hjarnø. For terms of use please visit http://www.copenhagenmediacenter.com/

Add.Title: Sunset at Tisvilde Beach
Add.Description: Copenhagen: A visit to one of the region's tempting beaches is a feast for all the senses, with the wide skies, the wind in your hair and the taste of salt on your skin. Photographer: Christian Alsing. For terms of use please visit http://www.copenhagenmediacenter.com/

Add.Title: Louisiana museum - kids make their own art
Add.Description: Copenhagen: The Louisiana Museum of Modern Art, located directly on the shore of the Øresund Sound in Humlebæk, north of Copenhagen, is the most visited art museum in Denmark with an extensive permanent collection of modern and contemporary art as well as a comprehensive programme of special exhibitions. Photographer: Ty Stange. For terms of use please visit http://www.copenhagenmediacenter.com/

Add.Title: Restaurant Jacobsen
Add.Description: Copenhagen: The exclusive restaurant named after the designer Arne Jacobsen is situated north of Copenhagen by the sea. Photographer: Morten Bjarnhof. For terms of use please visit http://www.copenhagenmediacenter.com/

Add.Title: Finn Juhl's House - Ordrupgaard
Add.Description: Copenhagen: Finn Juhl’s own house is a textbook example of his project as an architect and as a furniture designer. It is composed of two blocks standing at right-angles to each other and joined by an entrance hall which opens to the garden. In one block is a large living room and a small study, while the second block houses the kitchen, dining room, bedrooms and bathroom. Photographer: Anders Sune Berg. For terms of use please visit http://www.copenhagenmediacenter.com/

Add.Title: Thorvaldsen Museum
Add.Description: Copenhagen: This frisky, Classicistic building was the first museum building in Denmark open for the common people of Copenhagen. The museum displays the works of Bertel Thorvaldsen who lived in Rome for nearly forty years, and built up a reputation as a world-famous sculptor. Photographer: Christian Alsing. For terms of use please visit http://www.copenhagenmediacenter.com/

The boats leave either from the Gammel strand or Nyhavn (New Haven) from morning till late afternoon every day. Photographer: Ty Stange. Add.Description: Copenhagen: Ny Carlsberg Glyptotek is a museum of ancient and modern art of international stature in the centre of Copenhagen, which houses over 10.000 works of art from the Mediterranean cradle of Western culture and from Denmark and France of the 19th and 20th centuries.
